english: Did you play with the teacher? What type of game was it?
Well done! Are you happy that you finished your game?
So you played a game with your teacher?
Did you enjoy your lunch? Can you tell me what you ate?
You had lunch with your friend? That sounds really nice! Can you tell me more about your friend?
localized: 친구랑 점심 먹었어? 너무 좋았겠다! 그 친구에 대해 더 자세히 말해줄래?

english: You ate together with your friend? What did both of you have for lunch?
localized: 친구랑 밥을 같이 먹었구나? 점심으로 뭘 먹었니?

english: That's great! What did you talk about with your teacher?
Which teacher did you talk to? Did it make you happy?
localized: 어떤 선생님이랑 얘기했어? 그래서 기분 어땠니?

english: Did you enjoy talking with your teacher?
What book did you read at school today?
Did you make a new friend today? What's their name?
localized: 오늘 새로운 친구를 만들었어? 친구 이름은 뭐야?

english: Did you enjoy your music class? What song did you learn?
localized: 음악 시간이 재미있었구나? 어떤 노래를 배웠니?

english: What was the most interesting thing you experienced at school?
How do you feel about your homework? Is there a lot?
You sound excited about playing outside! Let's get ready for the playground after the conversation.
localized: 밖에서 신나게 놀고 싶구나! 그럼 이따 대화 끝나고 놀이터 가자.

english: Do you want to take any of your favorite toys to the playground?
Which activities are you excited about at the playground? The swings, slides, or climbing?
localized: 놀이터에서 뭐하고 놀고 싶어? 그네, 미끄럼틀, 언덕 오르기?

english: Sorry to hear that you felt bored. Did something specific make you feel that way?
localized: 저런, 지루했구나. 어떤 게 너를 지루하게 했니?
